                <ol class="mt-6 list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-lg text-slate-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
                    <li>Attacker Contract calls <code class="bg-slate-200 px-1 rounded">withdraw()</code> on The DAO Contract.</li>
                    <li>The DAO checks attacker's balance (<span class="text-green-600 font-semibold">VALID</span>).</li>
                    <li>The DAO sends ETH to the Attacker Contract.</li>
                    <li>The ETH transfer triggers the Attacker's <code class="bg-slate-200 px-1 rounded">fallback()</code> function.</li>
                    <li>The <code class="bg-slate-200 px-1 rounded">fallback()</code> function immediately calls <code class="bg-slate-200 px-1 rounded">withdraw()</code> again (<strong class="text-red-600">RE-ENTERING</strong>).</li>
                    <li>Go back to Step 2. The DAO checks the balance again‚Äîit's still valid because it <strong class="text-red-600">hasn't been updated yet!</strong></li>
                </ol>
